org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api

Interface ILimitValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLimitValue, AbstractLimitValueProxy, LimitValue, LimitValueProxy

    public interface ILimitValue
extends com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto

    A data-access layer data-transfer-object interface for the LimitValue. The data-transfer-object class and proxy class implement this interface, as does the business-layer data-transfer-object class.

    An integer count that sets a boundary; the set of counts is a series of integer boundaries that the metering system uses to take its actions--usually the last one is the blocking limit, while the earlier ones provide warnings

    Stereotypes:

    • CompositeKey
    • Persistent

    Class is read/write: true

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
